Change our Future initiatives focus on and invest in the development of our youth. The Next Man Up Mentorship Program serves young black males in high school helping them become future leaders in business, education, politics and technology. Our I AM Youth Leadership Summit brings cultural awareness and diverse experiences to high school students of color to ensure equitable representation is at the forefront for our young leaders. Support our mission today visit @changeourfuturefund. 🙏🏾 #kidsfirst #youthdevelopment #mycausemycleats

Going undrafted is a moment I will never forget but it made me who I am today as a player. For those of you in the draft this year, if you are unfortunate to hear your name called do not get discouraged. It doesn’t matter how you got there. It matters what you do with what happens and what you’ve been given. Seize the moment. 

Get what you deserve. Earned not given!! 

Thank you @gmfb for having me on air today! Always a pleasure. #undrafted

As I celebrate another year of life, I am reminded about the importance of time. I have learned that time is not something to be wasted, but rather cherished and used wisely. It's important to prioritize the things that truly matter in life, such as spending time with loved ones, pursuing passions, and making a positive impact on the world. As I move forward into another year of life, I vow to make the most of my time and to never take it for granted. Here's to another year of making memories and cherishing every moment. ✌🏾🫶🏾 #33

As athletes often we are told shut up and play ball. Throughout history some of the most iconic athletes chose to speak out on social issues. Jim Brown, Muhammad Ali, John Wooten are deemed as trailblazers for recognizing their influence and using their voice to positively affect society. Today we have a social responsibility as athletes to those before us to fulfill our civic duties to affect change in our communities. Thank you to the city of Cleveland and @clevelandbrowns organization for recognizing the Ali Summit importance in the civil rights movement. This marker symbolizes courage, strength, and unity demonstrated by some of the greatest athletes of all time. Thank you for allowing me to be apart of history!
Had to bark for them to pay attention #theland #dawgpound

Attention Philadelphia Parents who have students in middle school and early high school! Is your child interested in Virtual Reality or E-Gaming and dream of turning their passion into a future career? Well, we're thrilled to announce an incredible opportunity coming to Philadelphia on 10/25/23 from 4:30PM to 6:30PM!

Black Meta Agency (@bmaweb3 ), in collaboration with the Change Our Future Foundation (@changeourfuturefund ) founded by Erika and Rodney McCleod (formerly of the Eagles and now with the Cleveland Browns), is bringing the world of VR & E-Gaming to #Philadelphia. We aim to introduce the city's youth to Healthcare Careers while harnessing the transformative power of Virtual Reality and E-Gaming.

Did you know that VR & E-Gaming can boost students' retention of information by an astounding 83% compared to traditional learning methods? This two-hour event is entirely FREE for students and will be held at the Lonnie E. Young Recreation Center, located at 1100 E Chelten St, Philadelphia, PA, from 4:30 PM to 6:30 PM.

During this event healthcare professionals will be sharing valuable insights on the synergy between technology and healthcare, along with guidance on how to enter this exciting industry. Plus, there will be snacks and prizes available for all students, as well as information on upcoming field trips that will enhance the learning experience later this year.

If you want your students to seize this amazing opportunity, please register them today! Thanks to our partners and team at Steam Your Dreams Roman Sudan Montagueo II for providing the e-gaming experience and Eric Brown, Jr. 💡 for leading our VR activities. Shoutout to Brittany Johnson for driving the coordination on behalf of Change Our Future Foundation. 

Register via eventbrite (search STEAM Fusion in Philadelphia or link in bio)

Disappointment, frustration, anger are all valid emotions as my 2023 season comes to an end. However I am thankful for this season of gratitude to reflect on the blessings God has provided over my 12 year career. Gods peace rules my heart giving me calmness and confidence entering this season of opportunity and growth. My biggest life lessons have occurred in times of hardship, I learned the true power of the mind! The lens we choose to look through during adverse moments is critical! Keep a clear lens do not allow your lens to be compromised or clouded by external factors. I believe Gods work is never by accident but always on time and purposeful. His purpose for us is greater than we can ever imagine. Excited to walk alongside him on this road to discovery and recovery!! 🙏🏾
GODS PLAN > OUR PLAN #Godsplan

Happy New Year! This past year God gifted me with a beautiful set of artwork to submerge in generating a multifaceted emotional experience. Art tends to tell a story for our own personal interpretation. It allows us to see ourselves in that moment, It is a way of seeing our inner world—our thoughts and beliefs. While this beautiful art collection taught me valuable life lessons it also equipped me with a set of tools to use throughout life. 2023 exhibit will serve as a remembrance of Gods timing and preparation! I will cherish it forever! Thank You in advance for 2024 masterpieces! 🙏🏾
